the yellow crane tower aka huanghelou modern in structure ancient in lore and legend the original tower is presumed to have been first built in approximately 220 ad the tower has been destroyed and reconstructed numerous times was burned last according to some sources in  1884  jung changs book moa the unknown story however refers to mao ascending the yellow crane pavilion in 1927 to look across the vastness of the yangtze suggesting a later date for its destruction complete reconstruction took place in  1981  the reconstruction utilized modern materials and even includes an elevator yet in outward appearance and detail is true in spirit to the traditional design of the tower through the centuries
